****The board game "Don't be angry" now also in Counterstrike: Source!****



*** W knobs are to throw the dice***
*** A fields are some actionfields ***

Rules:

Only if all 4 players are in the startbase, the team is permitted to throw the dice 3 times.
By throwing a 6 the team is permitted to throw the dice again.
The startfield has to be evacuated immediately.
If the team had thrown a 6 3 times in a row, one of the team hast to go back to the start.
If someone is able to kick out an enemie, he/she had to do that. If somebody doesnt kick out an enimie, SHE/HE has to go back to the start (who denied the kick).
Only one figure (one terrorist) is allowed on one field.
Only the team whose turn it is, should speak!
If the cube lies on the corner, the bigger cube side counts. If no cube side is the bigger one you have to throw the dice again.




Actionfields:

If you had thrown the dice and you get on an actionfield, you have to press that!





Action of the fields are e.g.:

Throw the dice again..
Move fields forward/backward.
back to the start.
And immunity for the kick of the enemies for one round.



Have Fun!
___________________________________________________________________________________________

****Das Brettspiel "Mensch ärger dich nicht" nun auch in Counterstrike: Source!****



*** W Knöpfe sind zum Würfeln ***
*** A Felder sind Aktionsfelder ***

Regeln:

Nur wenn alle aus einem Team in der Startbase sind, darf das Team 3 Mal würfeln!
Mit einer Sechs kommt man raus.
Bei einer gewürfelten Sechs darf/muss man nochmal würfeln.
Das Startfeld muss sofort geräumt werden!
Wenn man 3 Sechser hintereinander würfelt muss man zurück an den start.
Wenn man einen Gegner rauschmeißen kann, muss man dies tun. Sollte man den Gegner nicht schmeißen muss man selbst zurück an den Start.
Auf ein Feld passt nur eine Figur (ein Terrorist).
Reden sollte wen möglich nur die Manschaft die am Zug ist!
Würfelkippe gibt es nur wenn keine der beiden angezeigten flächen eindeutig größer ist!




Aktionsfelder:

Wenn man gewürfelt hat und landet auf einem Aktionsfeld, muss man dieses drücken!





Aktionen die von den Feldern aus gehen sind z.B:

Nochmal würfel..
Felder vor/zurück.
Zurück an den Start.
Und imun für eine Runde vor dem Rausschmiss einer generischen Manschaft.




Viel Spaß!

nyro's SDK Steam Group **A NOBLOCK PLUGIN IS REQUIRED TO PLAY THIS MAP** MG\_LT\_METROPOLIS\_V2 - 04-24-13 ======================= - Map by: nyro - **04-24-13** _v2 ------------------ - _v2 release - Fixed a LINUX crash related to game_ui **04-23-13** _v1 ------------------ - _v1 release A city themed tower map. Enjoy! This map is played in 2 round intervals, the first round you vote for a mode and spawn sides are chosen randomly. On the 2nd round spawns are alternated to keep things fair. Different modes unlock or lock different areas of the map, and are available to choose based on player count. The larger modes require more players to choose, however there is an override button that an admin can noclip to and +use to bypass this restriction. Below is a list of commands executed by the map. **Server Commands** +sv_airaccelerate 150 +sv_enablebunnyhopping 1 +mp_freezetime 0 +mp_startmoney 16000 +mp_buytime 5 **Soundtrack** ------------------ - Voting // Erik Satie Trois Gymnopédies - Secret // David Carretta - The Rebirth Please rate and/or comment, Thanks! -

nyro's SDK Steam Group - MG\_LT\_GLACIER - 12-28-11 ========================== - **NoBlock plugin is required to play this with more than 1 player** - **Some plugins rename players and cause teles not to work, some trail plugins may cause this** - **This map modifies sv\_gravity, it is set up to change back to 800 at the end of each round. I recommend putting sv\_gravity 800 in your server config incase the map changes mid-round.** **Description** ------------------ - A racing map based off of the popular minigame "iceskate". Players race to the end dodging various obstacles and hitting boosters to gain speed. **Features a random track generator so no 2 tracks are ever the same.** After each race players will battle it out in a randomized iceskate arena. Players that placed 1st -> 10th will be rewarded with weapons for the arena. The better your place the better your reward will be. - Choose between EASY, MEDIUM, and HARD difficulties for the track, or select BONUS to play a Long Jump competition! **Author** ------------------ - Map by: nyro - **Custom Textures** ------------------ - CHECK EM **Music Recommendations** ------------------ - qr **Feedback & Testing** ------------------ - CHECK EM - hlstriker - N.O.L.F. - qr - TonyCip - Detonater - Kanka - [bella basic] **Special Thanks** ------------------ - cfoust // Author of Propper. You will be able to join once the current race ends. - Reaching the far end of Long Jump will prevent you from being teleported on the following rounds. - If the generated track is very long, the finish line tele may not work. This is a team based puzzle map. The goal of the map is extremely simple -> reach the top of the map. But that's easier said then done. The map contains 25 unique levels, with each level presenting it's own challenges. However, you're not working in first person view. This is a top down puzzle game, and because of this every person needs to look unique to be able to tell which character you are. So, there is quite a selection that you can choose from. You can choose to be squares, circles, triangles, and mixes of all three shapes (see screenshots).

Due to the difficulty however, everyone is expected to die. But that's been accounted for. Initially, the entire server starts off with 5 lives, and every time everyone has died, you will lose a life, and everyone will respawn. Once you reach 0 lives, it's game over, and you must start again from scratch. However, every time a level is beaten, everyone is respawned and get's to attempt that level.

So what do the levels look like? The levels all take place at the same area, in a 5x5 grid. Repeating patterns appear, and once a brown block hits you, you are dead. Screenshots don't do this justice however, but you can see a sample in the screenshots. Since they do not clearly show what each level looks like, so watch the video below (which is from StarCraft 2) to see the gameplay. Each level is possible (since I have beaten it to test!), but some require creative thinking to pass (in the more difficult levels). 

Made for the SteamGamers Mapping Contest. The map contains 48 spawns.
